<HEADLINE>
MARINOVICH SIGNS WITH ARENA LEAGUE'S AVENGERS 
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Former USC and Raiders quarterback Todd Marinovich
will play football in Los Angeles again, after signing a contract
Saturday with the L.A. Avengers of the Arena Football League.
</P>
<P>
   It's another comeback attempt for Marinovich, 30, who spent last
season with British Columbia of the Canadian Football League before
being released.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought it would be a great match. It's an opportunity to
play and have some fun,'' Marinovich said. ``It's definitely an
adjustment to go from a huge field (in Canada) to a small field in
an indoor stadium.''
</P>
<P>
   Marinovich is best known from his days with USC (1989-90) and
the Raiders (1991-92). He also drew headlines in 1997 when he was
sentenced to six months in jail after pleading guilty to a felony
charge of cultivating marijuana. He served three months.
</P>
<P>
   As part of a standard Arena League contract, Marinovich will
undergo random drug tests, according to Avengers coach Stan Brock.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've had problems in the past, but it's all been a learning
experience,'' Marinovich said. ``Hopefully, we learn from them and
move on.''
</P>
</TEXT>
