   SATURDAY, April 1
</P>
<P>
   AFRICA-HUNGER-$ADV01 _ NIGERIA _ One of the fundamental issues
hindering Africa's development is inadequate agricultural
production. Many nongovernmental organizations are trying to
address this with programs intended to teach farmers methods to
increase their yields. The Carter Center's Global 2000, in
partnership with the Japanese Sasakawa Africa Association, has
helped started hundreds of small-scale farm programs that have
increased crop yields by 200 percent to 300 percent by applying
technologies and materials already available in Africa. But the
programs are fragile propositions that rely on often unpredictable
governments fighting military and paramilitary factions to provide
a window in which they can work. (Roughton).
</P>
<P>
   With Photos.
</P>
