   CUBA-STORIES-$ADV16 _ HAVANA _ Today's Cuba from the perspective
of the ``average'' Cuban on the street. This will be several
stories from interviews done with several different people and
families in Cuba. As we live and eat in their homes for several
weeks, we talk to them about everyday life, its trials and
tribulations. We ask them about their hopes and dreams living in
this ``socialist'' society. We ask them what they really think of
the United States and Americans. We ask what has changed for them
in the last 40 years., and the impact of the U.S. economic embargo.
And just how do they keep those old Chevys running? (Williams).
