<P>
   INTERNET-TAX (Undated) _ Making the Internet tax-free was such a
popular idea 14 months ago that Congress overwhelmingly passed the
Internet Tax Freedom Act and created a commission to further that
goal. But as e-commerce has grown, retailers and other companies
are rethinking their stance. Business interests from the Chamber of
Commerce on down are now organizing to demand that sales taxes be
applied to products wherever they are sold. The issue will come to
a head Monday and Tuesday as the congressional panel holds its
final meeting. By David Cay Johnston.
