not among the giant mobile depicting the planets of our solar
system. And by leaving it out, astronomers at the planetarium are
rekindling an old argument: just what makes a planet a planet,
anyway? By Dan Zehr. (900 words)
</P>
<P>
   LIVE-FUNERALS (New York) _ The Internet, already swarming with
aquarium-cams, traffic-cams and this-is-my-room-cams, is starting
to attract a new kind of live event _ funerals. While the numbers
are still small, some funeral home owners say Webcasting a funeral
helps those who can't be there celebrate the life of the dearly
departed from afar. By Kate Dawson. (900 words)
</P>
<P>
   STREET-NEWS (New York) _ Newspapers that benefit the homeless,
through offering them a voice as well as income from selling them
on the street, are increasing in number and reach. And the
longest-running editor of Street News in New York, which calls
itself the oldest active homeless paper in the nation, says he has
a mission _ to keep that voice alive. By William Siss. (975 words)
</P>
