   &QL; 
 &UR; TECHBUILD _ &LR;  Manufacturing _ to many the essence of the old economy
_ turns out to be one of the fastest-growing and most lucrative
segments of the new one. At least that's the case for a small group
of companies that specialize in cranking out circuit boards, cell
phones and other high-tech items on contract to the companies who
design and market such products. Over the past decade the major
players in this build-for-hire business have recorded dizzying
rates of growth. With two sidebars.  &UR; BY HENRY &LR; 
 &UR; NORR &LR;
