 &UR; BIOSCOPE _  &LR; San Francisco artist Marilyn Donahue has proposed a
simple way for people to protest the patenting of human genes. She
suggests people copyright their own DNA. ``It probably won't have
much legal effect,'' admitted the former biology researcher turned
artist. ``For me, this is really about making people take an
interest in where biotechnology is going.''  &UR; COLUMN BY TOM &LR; 
 &UR; ABATE &LR;
