 &UR; DSL &LR;   &UR; _  &LR; It took Pacific Bell six technicians and more than nine
hours on four different days to install Joe Ramos' high-speed
Internet line in Half Moon Bay. On another date, workers simply
didn't show up at all. The installation process didn't go any more
smoothly for San Francisco filmmaker Ronald Levaco, who also
ordered a digital subscriber line, which offers superfast Internet
access over conventional copper phone lines. But SBC Communications
of Texas, which owns Pac Bell, says it is on the verge of making
DSL installation so simple that most customers can install the line
themselves in 30 minutes to an hour.  &UR; BY TODD &LR; 
 &UR; WALLACK &LR;
