<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, MARCH 18
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Monday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(ss) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-POPE-APOLOGY-NYT (moved Sunday, March 12)
</P>
<P>
   A translation of excerpts sent Sunday, March 12 from Pope John
Paul II's homily asking forgiveness for the church included an
incorrect version of a sentence referring to Christian victims and
their persecutors. According to the transcript now available on the
Vatican's Web site (www. &QL; 
vatican.va), the pope said, ``Just as the victims of such abuses
forgave them, so let us forgive as well'' _ not ``As we forgive the
victims of these offenses, we also forgive ourselves.''
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-GEEK-NOTES-NYT (moved Wednesday, March 15)
</P>
<P>
   A Circuits column sent on Wednesday, March 15 about the online
version of the Oxford English Dictionary misstated the price of
institutional subscriptions. They start at $795 and depend on the
customer's size, the number of users and other factors; there is no
universal price.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-BUILDING-WEBPAGES-ART-2TAKES-NYT (moved Wednesday, March
15)
</P>
<P>
   A Circuits article sent on Wednesday, March 15 about making
personal Web pages gave an incomplete name for the editor of
efuse.com, a site for page designers. He is Daniel Will-Harris, not
Will Harris.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
