<P>
   A translation of excerpts sent Sunday, March 12 from Pope John
Paul II's homily asking forgiveness for the church included an
incorrect version of a sentence referring to Christian victims and
their persecutors. According to the transcript now available on the
Vatican's Web site (www. &QL; 
vatican.va), the pope said, ``Just as the victims of such abuses
forgave them, so let us forgive as well'' _ not ``As we forgive the
victims of these offenses, we also forgive ourselves.''
</P>
